search_results.title: THE BAND
search_results.snippet: Daimh are West Highland Music's proudest exponents. Daimh, the Gaelic word for Connection, perfectly describes the electrifying musical interplay.

search_results.title: Dàimh
search_results.snippet: Dàimh (pronounced "dive") is a folk band which performs in Scottish Gaelic. Its members are Angus MacKenzie (whistle/bagpipes), Gabe McVarish (fiddle)

search_results.title: Daimh: HOME
search_results.snippet: About Daimh. Daimh – Gaelic Supergroup and un-challenged champions of straight in the eye Highland music are based around West Lochaber and the Isle of Skye.
